<section class="seo-content">
  <h2>How to play the Mini Crossword</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The board is a quick 5&times;5 grid with a short list of Across and Down clues.</li>
    <li>Tap any white square to select it, then type letters; tap the same square again to switch between Across and Down.</li>
    <li>Read the highlighted clue at the top and fill in the answer one letter at a time.</li>
    <li>Use the arrow keys to move around the grid, and the clue list to jump straight to a specific entry.</li>
    <li>Stuck on a square? Use Check to test your letters, or Reveal a letter, word, or the whole puzzle.</li>
    <li>Fill every square correctly to stop the timer and finish the puzzle.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Tips &amp; strategy</h2>
  <p>
    Start with the clues you are sure of and let the crossings do the rest. Every letter you place sits in
    both an Across and a Down answer, so a confident fill instantly gives you a free letter in the
    intersecting word. The short three- and four-letter entries are usually the easiest way in.
  </p>
  <p>
    If a clue reads as a plural or a past tense, pencil in the likely S or ED ending &mdash; those almost
    always land in the right spot and unlock neighbors. When you are truly stuck, the Check button confirms
    which letters are right without giving the answer away. And because the grid is only twenty-five squares,
    a single solved corner often cascades into the whole puzzle within seconds.
  </p>

  <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
  <details>
    <summary>Is the Mini Crossword free?</summary>
    <p>Yes &mdash; it is a free daily mini crossword with no paywall, no account, and no app to install. Just open the page and solve.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>When does the daily crossword reset?</summary>
    <p>A new 5&times;5 grid goes live once a day. Come back tomorrow for the next one, or solve earlier grids in the <a href="/crossword/archive">archive</a>.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>How is this different from the NYT Mini?</summary>
    <p>It is the same bite-sized format &mdash; a 5&times;5 daily crossword you can finish in a minute or two &mdash; but ours is a free NYT Mini alternative with no paywall. It is built by the team behind a science newsletter, runs in any browser, and tracks your time on a daily leaderboard.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Can I play past crosswords?</summary>
    <p>Yes. The <a href="/crossword/archive">crossword archive</a> lets you go back and solve earlier daily grids whenever you like.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Do I need an account?</summary>
    <p>No sign-up needed. Your progress is saved in your browser, and you only enter a nickname if you want your solve time on the daily leaderboard.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>What happens if I reveal letters?</summary>
    <p>You can reveal a letter, a word, or the entire puzzle if you get stuck. Revealing the puzzle keeps you from appearing on the leaderboard, but it is a handy way to learn a tricky answer.</p>
  </details>

